[4] Europe (Bulgaria)
Date: Tue 11 Apr 2017
Source: Bulgarian National Television (BNT) News [edited]
https://www.bnt.bg/en/a/new-measles-cases-reported-in-bulgaria


There are 14 laboratory-confirmed cases of measles in Bulgaria. The DNA analysis of Bulgaria's National Centre on Infectious and Parasitic Diseases showed on 31 Mar [2017], the virus is the same [as] the one reported in Romania.

Many measles cases have been reported in Italy, France, and Germany, where the infection is endemic. People who often travel to those countries should be monitored.

Health specialists advise bus and lorry drivers, who return from those countries to avoid close contact with many people in the period following their return in order to prevent dissemination of the diseases.

