7 countries, where vaccination rates are low, have had the worst outbreaks in Europe:
Case numbers February 2016 - January 2017:
France 93
Germany 369
Poland 140
Switzerland 7
Italy 1020
Romania 1995
Ukraine 111

Early information for February 2017 indicates new infections are continuing to rise sharply, the WHO warned. It is important that every country immunize their populations to the 95 percent level required to fully prevent outbreaks when infected individuals introduce virus.

